==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*nefe'', from Indo-European ''*nepot-''.

''Germanic cognates:'' Old Frisian [[neva]], Old Saxon [[nevo]] (Dutch [[neef]]), Old High German [[nevo]] (German [[Neffe]]), Old Norse [[nefi]].

''Indo-European cognates:'' Avestan ''napāt-'', Latin [[nepos|nepōs]], Old Irish [[necht]] (Cornish [[noith]]), Russian [[нестера]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'neva/

===Noun===
'''nefa''' ''m''
# a [[nephew]]
# a [[grandson]]
# a [[stepson]]

